  "texts": [
    "Control results of drag coefficient C D for different sensor configurations in PM-Dynamic cases are presented in figure 12.",
    "In the configuration with N = 2, two sensors are placed at y = ±0.25, and for N = 1, only one sensor is placed at y = 0.25.",
    "Other configurations are consistent with (2.3).The C D curves in figure 12 show that as the number of sensors is reduced from 64 to 2, RL control achieves the same level of performance with minor discrepancies due to randomness in different learning cases.",
    "However, if RL control uses observations from only one sensor at y = 0.25, performance degradation can be observed in the asymptotic stage with 19.79 % on average less drag reduction.",
    "The inset presents the relationship between the number of sensors and asymptotic drag coefficient C D. These results indicate a limit on sensor configuration for the use of the NARX-modelled controller to stabilise the vortex shedding.To understand the cause of performance degradation in the N = 1 case, the pressure measurements from two sensors in both baseline and PM-Dynamic cases are presented in figure 13."
